[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'At this point, everyone knows that packaging is crucial for your YouTube videos. If your title and thumbnail never get clicked, you get no views, no conversions, and no growth. But very few people know just how much AI has revolutionized the packaging game for YouTube over the past few months. I\'ve'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'been using a tool called Pixels to handle all my packaging. And in just the last month alone, my views across all channels increased by 40%. And so, in this video, I\'m going to break down exactly how Pixels performs, what it actually helps with, and whether it\'s'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the best AI packaging tool you should be using for your YouTube channel. I\'ll leave a link down in the description for Pixels. When you first sign into Pixels, this is the window you\'ll see. Before we get into the main area, there are a couple of additional features I want to'

[00:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'mention. The first one is the model down here at the bottom. Always make sure you have the highest one selected, which in my case is this one right here. And you can also pick between different formats, either short form or long form videos. We\'re going to be sticking with long'

[00:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'form for this video. There\'s also a button for tutorials. I\'m going to walk you through everything that\'s inside here, but if you ever get stuck on something or you forget how a feature works, you can always check out one of the short tutorials. All right, with that out of the way, let\'s head into'

[01:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'some of the options inside the main prompt window. Up at the top, you can choose between four different ways of using pixels. You can prompt for a thumbnail, you can recreate a thumbnail, you can edit a thumbnail, write a title, and analyze an already existing'

[01:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'thumbnail. The analyze feature is super useful if you already have some videos uploaded on your channel because now you can analyze all of the thumbnails and improve them. I personally jump between all five of these depending on what I\'m working on. But I\'ll show you the exact'

[01:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'moments where each one makes sense for me. But what I can already tell you is that the most exciting one is prompting for a thumbnail. In the bottom left, you also have an option to select personas and styles, which are two of the most powerful features in pixels. I\'ll tell'

[01:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you more about them in just a second. I want to start with the titles first because that one is super useful as well, and it\'s actually a feature I use a lot. I\'m honestly not the best at titles myself, so having something that gives me a base to start from saves me a lot of decision fatigue. There are two'

[01:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'main ways you can use this feature. The first one is by just typing something in the prompt window using your keyboard and writing out whatever your video is about. The other method, which I personally use a lot when I\'m making titles, is this little microphone button down here in the bottom right. If you'

[02:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'click it, it starts a voice recording, and it\'ll record whatever you say, and then transcribe it into the prompt window. It makes it super easy and convenient because you can literally just hop in, open a new chat, talk through your overall video idea, and it\'ll turn that into three title options'

[02:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for [music] you. Because I\'m making a video right now, I\'m just going to type my idea in here. but it works the same way. So, I\'ll write make a title for a video about a 12-week weight loss plan made for beginners and focused around losing belly fat. Then, I\'ll hit the generate button and it starts generating'

[02:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'three title options for me. All three of them look pretty good. They all have the ideal length for a YouTube title and they\'re formatted in a proper YouTube style, which is really nice. Usually, if you try to do this through chat GPT, you have to go back and forth a bunch of'

[02:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'times until it finally understands how to make an actual YouTube title, but here it just gets it right away. There are also a couple of things you can do with each title that make this feature even more powerful. If I click on the second one over here and open the three'

[02:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'dots on the right, I get a few options. I can rewrite it, reverb it, shorten it, lengthen it, or emphasize. So, if I click on reverb, it\'ll start generating a new version of that same title. And it changed up the wording a bit, which'

[03:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'makes it stand out even more. It uses another word for lose, and now it says melt, which is a really cool way of sticking to the same idea, but switching up the language. It acts like a little pattern interrupt for your viewer. There\'s also one more feature I want to test out, and that\'s the brainstorm'

[03:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'feature. Here you have a ton of options you can add in. You can make the title more extreme, more positive, clever, or dramatic. There\'s literally a ton of variations to pick from. This brainstorm feature is great because you can pick a title you already like, run it through'

[03:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'one or two of these variations, and then end up with a few strong contenders. I use this all the time when I\'m stuck between two ideas, and it usually gives me a variation I wouldn\'t have thought of myself. Then you can put those into your YouTube video as multiple title'

[03:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'tests and YouTube will automatically rotate them. It\'ll figure out which one performs best with your audience. So you can get winning titles straight from pixels right away. But now that we\'re done with the titles, let\'s head over to the next feature, which is the thumbnail'

[03:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'creation. So I\'ll head over to the prompt window. A mistake a lot of people make here is making their prompt too vague. So something like a man excited about his new car. That just doesn\'t give the tool enough context to really understand what you want it to do. You'

[04:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'always want to be more specific. And there are two ways you can do that. You can either just be more specific in the way you type your prompts, or you can use the dictation feature. The biggest difference between the dictation feature inside the thumbnail generator versus the title generator is that inside the'

[04:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'thumbnail generator, you also have the enhanced prompt feature. This takes everything you say and turns it into a properly structured prompt. So, it\'s definitely a feature I recommend you use every single time. Now, let\'s make a thumbnail from scratch. I\'m just going'

[04:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to write this prompt right here. Make a thumbnail for this video title. The three-wheeler that required a license to kill. Use an ultraistic image of a reliant robin. Text must be tilt on site. Then I\'m going to click generate. And let\'s check out the result. What we'

[04:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'get back is a really cool thumbnail of this three- wheeled car. This could work out as a really good thumbnail for a video on this car\'s history. But Pixels has one of the most useful features that I\'ve seen across any other tool. And that is this virality score right here.'

[04:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
