[06:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'walk you through how they work. The personas feature is a way to train a model on a specific face, either yours or someone else\'s, and then the model can automatically use that face inside your generations. To create one, you want to click on personas, click on the'

[06:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'create button, and then give a name to your persona. After that, you upload at least 10 different images, but I always recommend going with at least 15, where you include photos from different angles, lighting setups, and perspectives so the model has the most'

[07:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'material to train on. I personally use this feature a lot when creating or testing out different angles of thumbnails. Once you have that, you just click generate, and the model will train itself on this person, and then it will show up in the list over here. The next'

